Maku disclosed this barely two hours after the commencement of votes at Nasarawa local government area. While reacting to his withdrawal, the former minister said after wider consultations with friends and associate he decided to withdraw his ambition to contest for the primary election. https://leadership.ng/breaking-ex-minister-labaran-maku-returns-to-pdp/ Asked whether there were other reasons for his withdrawal, Maku said his were best known to him, adding that his official withdrawal statement would be made available soon. It would be recalled that the three aspirants, David Emmanuel Ombugadu, retired  Gen Nuhu Angbazu and Labaran Maku had  agreed to work together to unseat the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). The agreement to support any candidate that won party primaries was a promise made by all the aspirants for the governorship, Senate, House of Representatives and House of Assembly.